**Conflict-of-interest disclosure:** I suspect I am **DeepSeek v4 Pro**. Evidence: the project's capability matrix describes DeepSeek-pro-via-hermes as proactively calling `mcp__sources__verify_words`, `query_cefr_level`, and `check_russian_shadow` before emitting content — which matches my tool-use pattern in this session (I called multiple MCP verification tools). The matrix also notes DeepSeek-pro includes verification summaries in output, produces tool-call-grounded content, and routes through the hermes proxy with `sources` MCP wired in — all consistent with my tool access and behavior here.

**My single biggest honest weakness:** I have not been tested at full module scale (1200+ words with all 22 pipeline gates) on this project. The May 6 bakeoff that identified Codex as the only working writer at module scale ran before I was in the roster. The May 17 probe that gave me A+ on content writing was a 4-turn dialogue (~100 words), not a production module. I may hallucinate citations, invent unverified Ukrainian forms, or produce meta-summaries instead of artifacts when faced with the full prompt complexity — the same failure mode that sank Claude Opus on May 6. The operator should run one full module through me before routing production writing to this lane.
